<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-09T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-09T01:00:00-05:00" n="60" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/1997:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-09T07:00:00+01:00">April 9,
                                    1940—7 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Norwegian Government left for Hamar 3 hours inland from Oslo at 7 a.m. I
                            am proceeding there by motor with other heads of missions. All Foreign
                            Service Officers remaining in Oslo. At request of British and French
                            Ministers this Legation has taken over British and French interests.
                            Oslo is quiet, as public has not yet realized situation. Foreign Office
                            states that Norwegian forces are resisting the German advance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>